How to build a stable FLEX system that works reliably 
at Crystal frequency from 4MHz to 20MHz 
and ambient temperature of 18-38 degrees Celsius.

Some problems with 5 Mhz bus 
and ambient temperature from 35 degrees Celsius and higher.

The 74LS491 chips on the IDE card become too hot and cause disk problems.
Replacing the 74LS491 with GAL22V10-15 prevents this.
Because the GAL decreases its Icc with increasing temperature?

A second critical point found, the 'NOT LINKED' startup message, is this.
The IDE card becomes very sensitive to the supply voltage at higher temperatures.
With the 74LS461, the voltage must be 5.0V or more to boot.
With the GALs the voltage must be 4.9V or more to boot.

For a stable system within the above ranges.:
 1- Replace the 2 pieces 74LS461 with 2 pieces GAL22V10-15.
 2- Supply voltage on the BUS card between 5.0 and 5.1 Volt.
 3- Do not use the female connector of the power adapter (these are unreliable).
    Solder the 5V wires to the back-plane!
 4- Place a USB fan under the system for cooling.



